[SN]TITLE[SN]
Gloucestershire and Wiltshire trio charged over safe thefts

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three men have been charged over the theft of safes across south-west England and the West Midlands.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
They were among seven people arrested during police raids on a number of addresses in Gloucestershire and Wiltshire on Thursday.
Jesse Gregory, 49, of Brinkworth, and two Gloucester men - David Royles, 53, and Joseph Butler, 24 - are charged with conspiring to commit a burglary.
They are due to appear at Swindon Crown Court on 19 June.
The three were remanded in custody after earlier appearing at Swindon Magistrates' Court.
Four others have been released on bail pending further inquiries.
